headline: Nvidia earnings & comments from CEO Jensen Huang: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, Aug. 27. In the morning, Williams-Sonoma (WSM) and Abercrombie & Fitch (ANF) will report quarterly earnings results. In the afternoon, Nvidia (NVDA), CrowdStrike (CRWD), Snowflake (SNOW), and HPE (HPE) will report quarterly earnings results. Nvidia is reporting second quarter results, and analysts are anticipating better-than-expected results due to strong demand for its artificial intelligence (AI) chips. Investors will be listening for commentary on the company's ability to sell chips in China. Tune in to Yahoo Finance on Wednesday, Aug. 27 at 4:15 p.m. for special coverage of Nvidia's quarterly results, followed by an exclusive interview with Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang at 6:40 p.m. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
